<!--*********************************************
            Solution
**********************************************-->  
<solution>
<p>The point $choice1 cannot be on the function. There is already a function output value (a <m>y</m>-value) in the table corresponding to the function input value <m>x = $choice1.x</m>. This is given in the table as <m>($x3, $y3)</m>.</p>
<p>Recall that, to be called a <ref uri="https://open.lib.umn.edu/algebra/chapter/topic-3-1/">function</ref>, a relationship can only have one output, or <m>y</m>-value, corresponding to each input, or <m>x</m>-value (the vertical line test).</p>
  
</solution>
</problem>
